description*.en: Linear Velocity, as the name implies deals with speed in a straight line, the units are often $km/hr$ or $m/s$ or $mph$ (miles per hour). Linear Velocity (v) = change in distance/change in time, where $v = \bigtriangleup d/\bigtriangleup t$
